Java Version: 
java version "1.4.1"
Java(TM) 2 Runtime Environment, Standard Edition (build
Java HotSpot(TM) Client VM (build 1.4.1-b21, mixed mode)

OS: Windows 2000

Batik 1.5 beta4

I have code that causes the JVM to terminate in every case.  I have copied 2 
samples of the relevent code below:

#1
------------------------------------------------------------------------       

    String parser = XMLResourceDescriptor.getXMLParserClassName();
    SAXSVGDocumentFactory f = new SAXSVGDocumentFactory(parser);
    Document doc = f.createDocument(uri);
    TIFFTranscoder transcoder = new TIFFTranscoder();
    TranscoderInput input = new TranscoderInput(doc);
    TranscoderOutput output = new TranscoderOutput(new java.io.FileOutputStream
("out.tiff"));
    transcoder.transcode(input, output);

#2
-------------------------------------------------------
    String parser = XMLResourceDescriptor.getXMLParserClassName();
    SAXSVGDocumentFactory f = new SAXSVGDocumentFactory(parser);
    Document doc = f.createDocument(uri);
    JPEGTranscoder t = new JPEGTranscoder();

    t.addTranscodingHint(JPEGTranscoder.KEY_QUALITY,
                         new Float(.8));
    TranscoderInput input = new TranscoderInput(doc);
    TranscoderOutput output = new TranscoderOutput(new java.io.FileOutputStream
("out.tiff"));
    transcoder.transcode(input, output);

---------------- END CODE ------------

Note that if I replace new TranscoderInput(doc) with new TranscoderInput(String 
systemId), the first example (with the JPEGEncoder) works but the second 
example (with the TIFFEncoder) does not.

Thanks in advance -- this is a great API.
